<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Richer de Forges, B." box="[792,1127,1978,2005]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref29070" refString="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Richer de Forges, B. (2007) A new species of deep-water spider crab of the genus Rochinia A. Milne-Edwards, 1875, from Guam (Crustacea: Brachyura: Majidae). Zootaxa, 1610 (1), 61 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1610.1.5" type="journal article" year="2007">Ng &amp; Richer de Forges 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 2013; 
<bibRefCitation author="Richer de Forges, B. &amp; Poore, G. C. B." pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="63 - 70" refId="ref30209" refString="Richer de Forges, B. &amp; Poore, G. C. B. (2008) Deep-sea majoid crabs of the genera Oxypleurodon and Rochinia (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Epialtidae) mostly from the continental margin of Western Australia. Memoirs of Museum Victoria, 65, 63 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 2008.65.6" type="journal article" year="2008">Richer de Forges &amp; Poore 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, B. Y. &amp; Richer de Forges, B. &amp; Ng, P. K. L." box="[293,463,2014,2041]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref27722" refString="Lee, B. Y., Richer de Forges, B. &amp; Ng, P. K. L. (2017) Deep-sea spider crabs of the families Epialtidae Macleay, 1838 and Inachidae MacLeay, 1838, from the South China Sea, with descriptions of two new species (Decapoda, Brachyura, Majoidea). European Journal of Taxonomy, 358, 1 - 37. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2017.358" type="journal article" year="2017">
Lee 
<emphasis box="[342,390,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tavares, M. S. &amp; Santana, W." box="[474,750,2014,2041]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="201 - 227" refId="ref30834" refString="Tavares, M. S. &amp; Santana, W. (2018) Refining the genus Rochinia A. Milne-Edwards, 1875: reinstatement of Scyramathia A. Milne-Edwards, 1880 and Anamathia Smith, 1885, and a new genus for Amathia crassa A. Milne-Edwards, 1879, with notes on its ontogeny (Crustacea: Brachyura: Epialtidae). Zootaxa, 4418 (3), 201 - 227. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4418.3.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Tavares &amp; Santana 2018</bibRefCitation>
), a revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lee &amp; Forges &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2019" box="[915,1016,2014,2040]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Rochinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[915,1016,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Rochinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now in preparation (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, B. Y. &amp; Richer de Forges, B. &amp; Ng, P. K. L." lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref27722" refString="Lee, B. Y., Richer de Forges, B. &amp; Ng, P. K. L. (2017) Deep-sea spider crabs of the families Epialtidae Macleay, 1838 and Inachidae MacLeay, 1838, from the South China Sea, with descriptions of two new species (Decapoda, Brachyura, Majoidea). European Journal of Taxonomy, 358, 1 - 37. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2017.358" type="journal article" year="2017">
Lee 
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
., 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). For the two new species described in this paper, they will both be provisionally placed in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Forges &amp; Ng, 2019" authorityName="Lee &amp; Forges &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2019" box="[1266,1367,153,179]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Rochinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="sensu lato">Rochinia</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="12" pageNumber="13" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
until a complete revision can be finished by the authors.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,153,323]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Therefore, with the description of two new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[841,897,225,251]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">PNG</collectingCountry>
and the transfer of four species out of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lee &amp; Forges &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2019" box="[1335,1436,225,251]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Rochinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1335,1436,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Rochinia</emphasis>
